sparql_query_kg2:
 Based on the information provided and the entity and relation mappings, the SPARQL query for KG2 (DBpedia) to find out how many films Leonardo DiCaprio starred in would be as follows:

```sparql
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX res: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>

SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?uri) AS ?c) WHERE {
  ?uri a dbo:Film ;
       dbo:starring res:Leonardo_DiCaprio .
}
```

This query counts the distinct URIs of entities that are instances of the `dbo:Film` class and have Leonardo DiCaprio as one of the starring actors.

