sparql_query_kg2:
 To produce a SPARQL query for KG2 (DBpedia) based on the given context and mappings, we need to translate the SPARQL query for Wikidata into an equivalent query for DBpedia.

Given the Wikidata SPARQL query:
```sparql
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>
SELECT DISTINCT ?value WHERE { wd:Q104123 wdt:P2130 ?value . }
```

And the entity and relation mappings:
```json
[
  {
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pulp_Fiction",
    "wikidata_ids": [
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q104123"
    ]
  },
  {
    "dbpedia_id": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/budget",
    "wikidata_ids": [
      "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/P2769"
    ]
  }
]
```

We can create the corresponding SPARQL query for DBpedia as follows:

```sparql
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX res: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?value WHERE {
  res:Pulp_Fiction dbo:budget ?value .
}
```

So, the final, complete SPARQL query for KG2 (DBpedia) is:

<sparql>
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX res: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?value WHERE {
  res:Pulp_Fiction dbo:budget ?value .
}
</sparql>

